    <header>
        <h1>Business Plan Template</h1>
        <p>A structured guide to help you build your business</p>
    </header>

    <div class="container">
        <h2>Introduction</h2>
        <div class="section">
            <p>Define your business idea, mission, and objectives clearly. Your mission should reflect what your business stands for and the problem it solves.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> A sustainable clothing brand focused on eco-friendly fashion and reducing environmental impact.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Market Analysis</h2>
        <div class="section">
            <p>Identify your target audience, competitors, and market trends. Understanding the demand for your product/service will help you position yourself strategically.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> A new coffee shop targeting young professionals in urban areas, offering a unique selection of organic and ethically sourced coffee.</p>
            <h3>Market Research Tools</h3>
            <h4>Free Tools:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Google Trends - Analyze search trends over time.</li>
                <li>Ubersuggest - Free keyword research and SEO tool.</li>
                <li>SurveyMonkey (Free Plan) - Conduct market surveys.</li>
                <li>Facebook Audience Insights - Understand audience demographics.</li>
            </ul>
            <h4>Paid Tools:</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>SEMrush - Comprehensive SEO and competitor analysis.</li>
                <li>Ahrefs - Backlink and keyword research.</li>
                <li>Moz Pro - Advanced SEO tracking.</li>
                <li>Statista - Industry reports and data analysis.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <h2>Business Model</h2>
        <div class="section">
            <p>Describe how your business will generate revenue and sustain growth. This includes your pricing strategy, cost structure, and revenue streams.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> A subscription-based model for an online learning platform offering exclusive courses and workshops.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Marketing Strategy</h2>
        <div class="section">
            <p>Outline your approach to reaching customers and growing your brand. This could include social media marketing, influencer collaborations, or traditional advertising.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> A digital marketing agency leveraging SEO and targeted Facebook ads to attract clients.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Operations Plan</h2>
        <div class="section">
            <p>Detail the logistics, resources, and team structure needed to operate. This includes your supply chain, employee roles, and operational workflow.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> An online store with a dropshipping model to minimize inventory costs while offering a diverse product range.</p>
        </div>

        <h2>Financial Plan</h2>
        <div class="section">
            <p>Include projected revenue, expenses, and funding requirements. Financial planning helps ensure your business remains sustainable and profitable.</p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong> A bakery estimating startup costs of $50,000 with expected monthly revenues of $10,000, seeking a small business loan for initial investment.</p>
            <table>
                <tr>
                    <th>Category</th>
                    <th>Estimated Cost</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Startup Costs</td>
                    <td>$50,000</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Monthly Revenue</td>
                    <td>$10,000</td>
